These steps allow the project to be reproduced and run locally.

Prerequisites
Python 3.9+

Install Git (if not installed).

A Gemini API Key (set as the GOOGLE_API_KEY environment variable).

Steps
Clone the Repository:

Bash

git clone YOUR_GIT_REPOSITORY_LINK
cd BizOps-Knowledge-Agent
Setup Environment:

Bash

python -m venv venv
.\venv\Scripts\activate
Install Dependencies:

Bash

pip install -r requirements.txt
Set API Key: Set your key as an environment variable in the active terminal session.

PowerShell

$env:GOOGLE_API_KEY="YOUR_ACTUAL_KEY_HERE"
Build the Knowledge Base (Indexing): (This step creates the ./chroma_db folder).

Bash

python ingest.py
Run the Working Demo:

Bash

streamlit run app.py
